{
  "texts": [
    "This methodology will significantly impact major platforms like Google, Facebook and X which previously only reported registered or active purchasing users.",
    "Complying will require recalibrating tracking and counting systems.",
    "Ongoing evaluation will help ensure proportionality across diverse entities during DSA phase-in.",
    "Expected platform impactsThese interlocking mechanisms aim to ensure online intermediaries take proactive, risk-based and accountable approaches to mitigate societal harms emerging from their services and design choices.Overall, the DSA signifies a paradigm shift for online intermediaries, moving away from self-regulation towards comprehensive accountability and public oversight mechanisms.",
    "It aims to compel platforms to take a more proactive, transparent and responsible approach to emerging online threats."
  ]
